        "text": "## pKa Values for Oxalic Acid (Ethanedioic acid)\n\nOxalic acid is a **diprotic acid** with **2 dissociation steps**:\n\n| Step | Equilibrium | pKa | T (°C) | I (mol/L) |\n|------|-------------|-----|--------|-----------|\n| 1st (Ka₁) | H₂L → HL⁻ + H⁺ | **−1.2** | 25 | 0.1 |\n| 2nd (Ka₂) | HL⁻ → L²⁻ + H⁺ | **3.8** | 25 | 0.1 |\n\n**Source:** NIST SRD-46 (ligand_8872, vlm_151532 & vlm_151494)",
